#. <section class="sutta" id="an4.23"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an4.23:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 4"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 4"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an4.23:0.2"
msgid "3. Uruvelavagga"
msgstr "3. At Uruvelā"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "an4.23:0.3"
msgid "23. Lokasutta"
msgstr "23. The World"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "an4.23:1.1"
msgid "“Loko, bhikkhave, tathāgatena abhisambuddho."
msgstr "“Mendicants, the world has been understood by a Realized One;"

msgctxt "an4.23:1.2"
msgid "Lokasmā tathāgato visaṃyutto."
msgstr "and he is detached from the world."

msgctxt "an4.23:1.3"
msgid "Lokasamudayo, bhikkhave, tathāgatena abhisambuddho."
msgstr "The origin of the world has been understood by a Realized One;"

msgctxt "an4.23:1.4"
msgid "Lokasamudayo tathāgatassa pahīno."
msgstr "and he has given up the origin of the world."

msgctxt "an4.23:1.5"
msgid "Lokanirodho, bhikkhave, tathāgatena abhisambuddho."
msgstr "The cessation of the world has been understood by a Realized One;"

msgctxt "an4.23:1.6"
msgid "Lokanirodho tathāgatassa sacchikato."
msgstr "and he has realized the cessation of the world."

msgctxt "an4.23:1.7"
msgid "Lokanirodhagāminī paṭipadā, bhikkhave, tathāgatena abhisambuddhā."
msgstr ""
"The practice that leads to the cessation of the world has been understood by "
"a Realized One;"

msgctxt "an4.23:1.8"
msgid "Lokanirodhagāminī paṭipadā tathāgatassa bhāvitā."
msgstr ""
"and he has developed the practice that leads to the cessation of the world."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli2.24"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an4.23:2.1"
msgid ""
"Yaṃ, bhikkhave, sadevakassa lokassa samārakassa sabrahmakassa "
"sassamaṇabrāhmaṇiyā pajāya sadevamanussāya diṭṭhaṃ sutaṃ mutaṃ viññātaṃ "
"pattaṃ pariyesitaṃ anuvicaritaṃ manasā, sabbaṃ taṃ tathāgatena "
"abhisambuddhaṃ."
msgstr ""
"In this world—with its gods, Māras, and Brahmās, this population with its "
"ascetics and brahmins, its gods and humans—whatever is seen, heard, thought, "
"cognized, searched, and explored by the mind, all that has been understood "
"by a Realized One."

msgctxt "an4.23:2.2"
msgid "Tasmā ‘tathāgato’ti vuccati."
msgstr "That’s why he’s called the ‘Realized One’."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "an4.23:3.1"
msgid ""
"Yañca, bhikkhave, rattiṃ tathāgato anuttaraṃ sammāsambodhiṃ abhisambujjhati "
"yañca rattiṃ anupādisesāya nibbānadhātuyā parinibbāyati, yaṃ etasmiṃ antare "
"bhāsati lapati niddisati sabbaṃ taṃ tatheva hoti, no aññathā."
msgstr ""
"From the night when a Realized One understands the supreme perfect awakening "
"until the night he becomes fully extinguished—through the natural principle "
"of extinguishment, without anything left over—everything he speaks, says, "
"and expresses is real, not otherwise."

msgctxt "an4.23:3.2"
msgid "Tasmā ‘tathāgato’ti vuccati."
msgstr "That’s why he’s called the ‘Realized One’."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "an4.23:4.1"
msgid "Yathāvādī, bhikkhave, tathāgato tathākārī, yathākārī tathāvādī."
msgstr "The Realized One does as he says, and says as he does."

msgctxt "an4.23:4.2"
msgid "Iti yathāvādī tathākārī, yathākārī tathāvādī."
msgstr "Since this is so,"

msgctxt "an4.23:4.3"
msgid "Tasmā ‘tathāgato’ti vuccati."
msgstr "that’s why he’s called the ‘Realized One’."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "an4.23:5.1"
msgid ""
"Sadevake, bhikkhave, loke samārake sabrahmake sassamaṇabrāhmaṇiyā pajāya "
"sadevamanussāya tathāgato abhibhū anabhibhūto aññadatthu daso vasavattī."
msgstr ""
"In this world—with its gods, Māras and Brahmās, this generation with its "
"ascetics and brahmins, gods and humans—the Realized One is the undefeated, "
"the champion, the universal seer, the wielder of power."

msgctxt "an4.23:5.2"
msgid "Tasmā ‘tathāgato’ti vuccati."
msgstr "That’s why he’s called the ‘Realized One’."

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "an4.23:6.1"
msgid "Sabbaṃ lokaṃ abhiññāya,"
msgstr "Directly knowing the whole world as it is,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.23:6.2"
msgid "sabbaṃ loke yathātathaṃ;"
msgstr "and everything in it,"

#. <br>
#. VAR: Sabbaṃ lokaṃ → sabbaloka (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "an4.23:6.3"
msgid "Sabbaṃ lokaṃ visaṃyutto,"
msgstr "he is detached from the whole world,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.23:6.4"
msgid "sabbaloke anūpayo."
msgstr "disengaged from the whole world."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "an4.23:7.1"
msgid "Sa ve sabbābhibhū dhīro,"
msgstr "That wise one is the champion"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.23:7.2"
msgid "sabbaganthappamocano;"
msgstr "who has escaped all ties."

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.23:7.3"
msgid "Phuṭṭha’ssa paramā santi,"
msgstr "He has reached ultimate peace:"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.23:7.4"
msgid "nibbānaṃ akutobhayaṃ."
msgstr "extinguishment, fearing nothing from any quarter."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "an4.23:8.1"
msgid "Esa khīṇāsavo buddho,"
msgstr "He is the Buddha, with defilements ended,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.23:8.2"
msgid "anīgho chinnasaṃsayo;"
msgstr "untroubled, with doubts cut off."

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.23:8.3"
msgid "Sabbakammakkhayaṃ patto,"
msgstr "He has attained the end of all karma,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.23:8.4"
msgid "vimutto upadhisaṅkhaye."
msgstr "freed with the end of attachments."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc9"></a>
msgctxt "an4.23:9.1"
msgid "Esa so bhagavā buddho,"
msgstr "That Blessed One is the Buddha,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.23:9.2"
msgid "esa sīho anuttaro;"
msgstr "he is the supreme lion,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.23:9.3"
msgid "Sadevakassa lokassa,"
msgstr "in all the world with its gods,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.23:9.4"
msgid "brahmacakkaṃ pavattayī."
msgstr "he turns the holy wheel."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc10"></a>
msgctxt "an4.23:10.1"
msgid "Iti devā manussā ca,"
msgstr "And so those gods and humans,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.23:10.2"
msgid "ye buddhaṃ saraṇaṃ gatā;"
msgstr "who have gone to the Buddha for refuge,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.23:10.3"
msgid "Saṅgamma taṃ namassanti,"
msgstr "come together and revere him,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.23:10.4"
msgid "mahantaṃ vītasāradaṃ."
msgstr "the great one, rid of naivety:"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc11"></a>
msgctxt "an4.23:11.1"
msgid "Danto damayataṃ seṭṭho,"
msgstr "‘Tamed, he is the best of tamers,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.23:11.2"
msgid "santo samayataṃ isi;"
msgstr "peaceful, he is the hermit among the peaceful,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.23:11.3"
msgid "Mutto mocayataṃ aggo,"
msgstr "liberated, he is the foremost of liberators,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.23:11.4"
msgid "tiṇṇo tārayataṃ varo."
msgstr "crossed over, he is the most excellent of guides across.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc12"></a>
msgctxt "an4.23:12.1"
msgid "Iti hetaṃ namassanti,"
msgstr "And so they revere him,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.23:12.2"
msgid "mahantaṃ vītasāradaṃ;"
msgstr "the great one, rid of naivety."

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.23:12.3"
msgid "Sadevakasmiṃ lokasmiṃ,"
msgstr "In the world with its gods,"

#. <br>
#. VAR: natthi me → natthi te (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "an4.23:12.4"
msgid "natthi me paṭipuggalo”ti."
msgstr "he has no counterpart.”"

#. </p></blockquote><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an4.23:12.5"
msgid "Tatiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
